[FILE:744:descriptions/desc.single]
Implementation of the 'viridis' - the default -, 'magma', 'plasma', 
    'inferno', and 'cividis' color maps for 'R'. 'viridis', 'magma',
'plasma', 
    and 'inferno' are ported from 'matplotlib' &lt;<a
href="http://matplotlib.org/">http://matplotlib.org/</a>&gt;, a 
    popular plotting library for 'python'. 'cividis', was developed by
Jamie R. 
    Nu√±ez and Sean M. Colby. These color maps are designed in such a way
that 
    they will analytically be perfectly perceptually-uniform, both in
regular 
    form and also when converted to black-and-white. They are also designed
to 
    be perceived by readers with the most common form of color blindness
(all 
    color maps in this package) and color vision deficiency ('cividis'
only).

